 <TerrainDef ParentName="FloorBase" >
  <defName>FineGoldFloorCoinA</defName>
    <label>shiny gold coin floor</label>
    <renderPrecedence>220</renderPrecedence>
	<color>(255,255,255)</color>
    <description>A floor made up of strewn about, loose gold coins. Walking on such grand amount of welath is the height of opulence.This floor takes a surprising amount of time to construct due to the awfully long coining procedure.</description>
    <texturePath>Things/Terrain/CoinFloor</texturePath>
    <pollutionTintColor>(0.95, 0.95, 0.93, 1)</pollutionTintColor>
    <isPaintable>true</isPaintable>
    <statBases>
      <WorkToBuild>8000</WorkToBuild>
      <Beauty>8</Beauty>
      <CleaningTimeFactor>0.4</CleaningTimeFactor>
    </statBases>
	
	<costList>
      <Gold>20</Gold>
    </costList>
	
    <researchPrerequisites>
      <li>Stonecutting</li>
	  <li>Smithing</li>
    </researchPrerequisites>
    <tags>
      <li>FineFloor</li>
    </tags>
    <constructionSkillPrerequisite>8</constructionSkillPrerequisite>
    <uiOrder>2089</uiOrder>
	<designatorDropdown>GS_Floor_Gold</designatorDropdown>
  </TerrainDef>
  
  <TerrainDef ParentName="FloorBase" >
  <defName>FineGoldFloorCoinB</defName>
    <label>shiny treasury floor</label>
    <renderPrecedence>220</renderPrecedence>
	<color>(255,255,255)</color>
    <description>When simple gold coins are not enough, one has to sate their lust for riches by supplementing their aurous diet with a good helping of precious stones and large bars of the aforementioned metal. Properly displaying and arranging such grand opulence takes time and effort, making this floor a tedium to construct.</description>
    <texturePath>Things/Terrain/CoinFloorGem</texturePath>
    <pollutionTintColor>(0.95, 0.95, 0.93, 1)</pollutionTintColor>
